"{\"uid\": \"news18.com-olympics-dutch-rower-florijn-keeps-it-in-the-family-with-olympic-gold-8989243.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Dutch rower Karolien Florijn dethroned reigning champion Emma Twigg in the women's single sculls on Saturday to add to her family's remarkable collection of Olympic gold medals.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"score\": 0.5519346615672145, \"rank\": 0.6436816355862405, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\"}, {\"begin\": 12, \"end\": 28, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karolien_Florijn\", \"score\": 0.999999999543661, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karolien Florijn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karolien_Florijn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karolien_Florijn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 26-year-old, the two-time reigning world champion, won her first Olympic gold with a time of 7min 17.28sec, finishing nearly two seconds ahead of New Zealand's Twigg (7:19.14).\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.9017330457601369, \"rank\": 0.07748027800173381, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Viktorija Senkute (7:20.85) won Lithuania's first-ever rowing medal with bronze.\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9995789731290832, \"rank\": 0.00041992332029923874, \"text\": \"Lithuania\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Florijn was ahead at the 500 metre mark and never relinquished her lead on the 2,000m course.\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her victory comes after her brother, Finn Florijn, won gold in quadruple sculls earlier this week while their father, Ronald Florijn, is a two-time Olympic champion -- at the 1988 Seoul Olympics and at the 1996 Atlanta Games.\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finn_Hudson\", \"score\": 0.9937651661822284, \"rank\": 0.005526287450901896, \"text\": \"Finn\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finn_Hudson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finn_Hudson\"}, {\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Florijn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ronald Florijn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Florijn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Florijn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It means the world to me,\\\" said Florijn.\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Winning a gold medal is what I wanted since I was born and doing it in the women's single sculls, amongst the best rowers in the world.\\\"\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 944, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Dutch rower paid tribute to dethroned champion Twigg.\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 950, \"end\": 955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"score\": 0.5519346615672145, \"rank\": 0.6436816355862405, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Emma pushed me until the last few metres, she really wanted to have a second gold medal,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am so inspired by her, she's one of the best rowers in the world and of course I wanted to win very badly and I managed.\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just executed my plan.\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have a great team around me and I am really thankful.\\\"\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Twigg, 37, said her legs \\\"gave up on me with about 100m to go\\\" but was delighted with her silver.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's up there with Tokyo for sure,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1443, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999930296393053, \"rank\": 6.946007704841679e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These Olympics were always about the cherry on top, and to come away with a medal is pretty special.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1571, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am stoked.\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swipe Left For Next Video  \\\"I have been to many Olympics and not had medals.\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am really proud that I laid it all out there.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Karolien is a fantastic sculler, so proud and pleased for her as well.\\\"\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CatchParis Olympics 2024